# Rust build artifacts
/target/
**/*.rs.bk
*.pdb

# Cargo lock file (for libraries, but we're keeping it for binary)
# Cargo.lock

# IDE files
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# OS files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Test and coverage artifacts
*.profraw
*.profdata
/tarpaulin-report.html

# Documentation build
/doc/

# Temporary files
*.tmp
*.temp

# SonarQube scanner runtime artifacts (see blitzy/scripts/run_sonarqube_scan.sh).
# The scanner writes its workspace cache under ``.scannerwork/`` in its CWD
# (which is REPO_ROOT for our driver), and a transient sonar-project.properties
# may be regenerated at runtime. Both are gitignored here so each scan leaves
# the working tree byte-identical to its pre-run state, per AAP §0.3.2 and
# §0.6.2.4. The user-named deliverable ``findings-config-i.json`` is the only
# scanner artifact that IS committed and is excluded from these rules.
.scannerwork/
sonar-project.properties
